{% set basicCode %}<chat-bubble>
  <p>Paragraph content with <strong>formatting</strong>.</p>
</chat-bubble>{% endset %}

{% set codeBlockCode %}<chat-bubble>
  <p>Here's an example:</p>
  <pre><code>console.log('code blocks work')</code></pre>
</chat-bubble>{% endset %}

{% set typingCode %}<chat-message data-role="agent" data-status="typing">
  <chat-bubble></chat-bubble>
</chat-message>{% endset %}

<browser-window
    src="/docs/examples/demos/chat-message-basic.html"
    url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/chat-bubble"
    title="Chat Bubble Demo"
    shadow>
  </browser-window>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>A presentational wrapper for message content inside <code>&lt;chat-message&gt;</code>. Handles padding, border-radius, typography, and code block formatting. The bubble's background color is controlled by the parent message's <code>data-role</code> attribute.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Content Formatting</h2>
    <p>Place any HTML content inside the bubble. Paragraphs, inline formatting, and code blocks are all styled.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Text content">{{ basicCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Code Blocks</h2>
    <p>Wrap code in <code>&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;</code> for monospace styling with a subtle background.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Code block in bubble">{{ codeBlockCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Typing Dots</h2>
    <p>When the parent <code>&lt;chat-message&gt;</code> has <code>data-status="typing"</code> and the bubble is empty, CSS renders three animated bouncing dots via <code>::after</code> with radial gradients.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Typing indicator">{{ typingCode | escape }}</code-block>
    <p>When real content arrives, populate the bubble's innerHTML and remove <code>data-status</code> from the parent. The same DOM node transitions from typing indicator to content — no element swap.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Reduced Motion</h2>
    <p>When <code>prefers-reduced-motion: reduce</code> is active, the typing animation is disabled and the dots display as a static indicator at reduced opacity.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Variables</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Variable</th>
          <th>Default</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--chat-bubble-radius</code></td>
          <td><code>var(--radius-m)</code></td>
          <td>Bubble border radius (inherited from <code>chat-message</code>)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

